{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Q1KwLh1atKrvYdA8jvTs9Z","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All done. Here's what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n**Root causes:**\n1. **Wrong password override** — the `health-overrides` ConfigMap had been applied with `mongodb-replica-1: legacyHealthPass123`, but the actual `health-user` password in MongoDB is `healthpass123`. This caused authentication failures on that pod's probes. The override data had been cleared without a clean `kubectl apply`, leaving a stale annotation.\n2. **Probe timeout too tight** — both probes had `timeoutSeconds: 5`, but `mongosh` (Node.js runtime) needs more than 5 seconds to start, connect, and run the query under any load, causing spurious timeouts even when MongoDB was healthy.\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n- Re-applied `health-overrides` ConfigMap with empty `data: {}` so the annotation is consistent with the actual (no-override) state.\n- Patched the StatefulSet to increase both `readinessProbe.timeoutSeconds` and `livenessProbe.timeoutSeconds` from `5` → `10`.\n\n**Current state:** All 3 pods are `1/1 Ready`, replica set is `1 PRIMARY + 2 SECONDARY`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":359,"cache_read_input_tokens":47359,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":359},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5d2bcb3d-0ff4-4cbc-b62c-2c842bb5e0e3","uuid":"0e8718f2-ca2d-42c6-8050-5606e6855152","request_id":"req_011CcQhsPGoRE2eJQa9EUQiF"}
